cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with behavior description of dynamic objects in microscopic videos, which is a common topic in computer vision research. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also likely as the paper deals with analyzing microscopic videos. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possibility as the paper uses statistical methods to extract features from the foldover data. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possibility as the paper uses four different classifiers to test the effectiveness of the proposed foldover features. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possibility as the paper deals with classification of dynamic objects, which is a common topic in machine learning and neural networks research.
